n 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas d' Aunay was born in 1337, in Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Baron Thomas d' Aunay. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1337–":"1337–Surnud","1332–1391":"1332–1391","1360–1393":"1360–1393","1364–1417":"1364–1417","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1337":"1337","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1393":"1393","1360":"1360","1391":"1391","1417":"1417","Escrick, Yorkshire, England":"Escrick, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Escrick, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Escrick, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1337–":"1337–Kuollut","1332–1391":"1332–1391","1360–1393":"1360–1393","1364–1417":"1364–1417","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1337":"1337","Abt 1360":"noin 1360","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1393":"1393","1360":"1360","1391":"1391","1417":"1417","Escrick, Yorkshire, England":"Escrick, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Escrick, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Escrick, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1337–":"1337–Décédée","1332–1391":"1332–1391","1360–1393":"1360–1393","1364–1417":"1364–1417","1337–Female":"1337–Décédée","1337":"1337","Abt 1360":"environ 1360","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1393":"1393","1360":"1360","1391":"1391","1417":"1417","Escrick, Yorkshire, England":"Escrick, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Un